 A Fidelity cash-in-transit vehicle was traveling from Bushbuckridge to Graskop yesterday when two vehicles allegedly pushed it off the road. According to CEO of Khulani Fidelity Service Group, Wahl Bartmann, the suspects in the two vehicles started shooting at the Fidelity vehicle. “They shot at the two front wheels of the vehicle as well as at the radiator. This is when our guys started to shoot back in defence,” Bartmann said. ALSO READ: BREAKING NEWS: Men posing as soldiers hit CIT van With the help of back-up security, no money or lives were lost. “We have also deployed extra safety teams in the area,” Bartmann said. The police were not available for comment. ALSO READ: VIDEO: CIT robbers hit Fidelity vehicle in Mbombela